# URL patterns lychee should skip during link checking.
# Replaces the old html-proofer per-link ignore mechanism with a URL-based
# allowlist. Each line is a regex matched against the full URL.

# Medium frequently rate-limits and blocks automated checks
^https?://(www\.)?medium\.com/

# Wikipedia anchored fragments with URL-encoded quotes are flagged as 404 even when valid
^https?://en\.wikipedia\.org/wiki/.*#.*%22

# LinkedIn requires authentication for most pages
^https?://(www\.)?linkedin\.com/

# Twitter/X aggressively blocks unauthenticated requests
^https?://(www\.)?(twitter|x)\.com/

# localhost and example domains used in code samples
^https?://localhost
^https?://127\.0\.0\.1
^https?://example\.(com|org|net)

# Intentionally-broken demo links in posts that document 404 behavior
^/2022/06/30/unhelpful-404s-for-jekyll/?$
